### Azure SignalR Serverless API Tests
### Use the REST Client extension to test these endpoints

@functionsUrl = http://localhost:7071
@groupName = test-group
@userId = test-user-1
@message = Hello from REST Client!

### Health Check
GET {{functionsUrl}}/api/health

### Negotiate SignalR Connection
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/negotiate
Content-Type: application/json

### Join Group
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/joinGroup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "groupName": "{{groupName}}",
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

### Send Message to Group
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "groupName": "{{groupName}}",
  "message": "{{message}}",
  "sender": "{{userId}}"
}

### Leave Group
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/leaveGroup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "groupName": "{{groupName}}",
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

### Test with Different User
@userId2 = test-user-2

### User 2 - Join Group
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/joinGroup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "groupName": "{{groupName}}",
  "userId": "{{userId2}}"
}

### User 2 - Send Message
POST {{functionsUrl}}/api/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "groupName": "{{groupName}}",
  "message": "Hi from User 2!",
  "sender": "{{userId2}}"
}
